        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 1:59PM CDT until June 8 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles south of
Wilburton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Eva, Hough, and Sturgis.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
